common_issues.title: Multiple PiecesOS Installations Detected
common_issues.description: Multiple PiecesOS installations detected on Windows 10 systems, causing installation failures.  Users need to uninstall all but one PiecesOS installation via "Add or Remove Programs" to resolve the issue. Affected users are running different Windows 10 builds and hardware configurations.

common_issues.title: Multiple PiecesOS Installations Detected
common_issues.description: Two Windows users encountered an error indicating multiple PiecesOS installations. This can lead to data corruption.  Users should uninstall all but one installation via 'Add or Remove Programs' to resolve the issue.  A macOS user reported being unable to open Pieces Core Services due to an UnauthenticatedUserException. Further investigation is needed for this case.

recommendations: Prioritize resolving the 'Multiple PiecesOS Installations Detected' issue on Windows by investigating the root cause and providing a permanent fix.
Investigate the 'Unable to open Pieces Core Services' error on macOS and determine if it's related to authentication issues or other factors.
Improve installation documentation or the installation process itself to prevent multiple PiecesOS installations.
Consider adding a check during installation to detect existing installations and prompt users to uninstall them.
